Configure Alexa to Work with Arduino IoT Cloud
Enable the Arduino IoT Cloud Skill in Alexa:

Open the Alexa app on your smartphone or go to the Alexa Skills Store on your computer.
Search for the "Arduino IoT Cloud" skill.
Click "Enable" to add the skill to your Alexa account.
Link Your Arduino Account to Alexa:

After enabling the skill, you will be prompted to link your Arduino account.
Log in with your Arduino credentials and grant permission for Alexa to access your Arduino IoT Cloud data.
Discover Devices:

Once the accounts are linked, Alexa will automatically discover the devices and variables from your Arduino IoT Cloud account.
You can also manually discover devices by saying, “Alexa, discover my devices.”
